$$\int_{s} \exp(x) \cdot f(\exp(x)) \, dx = \int_{\exp(s)} f(y) \, dy$$
where $s$ is a measurable set in $\mathbb{R}$, and $\exp(s)$ denotes the image of $s$ under the exponential function.

This is a standard result in measure theory, often referred to as the change of variables formula for the exponential function. In Lean, we will need to use the appropriate theorems for manipulating integrals under measurable transformations.

