The theorem `intervalIntegral.integral_comp` states that for a bijection $g: X \to Y$ with $g'$ (derivative) bounded on $s$, we have $\int_{s} f(g(x)) \cdot |g'(x)| \, dx = \int_{g(s)} f(y) \, dy$.

