- $f: \mathbb{R} \to \mathbb{R}$ is a function
- $g'(x) = \exp x$ is bounded on $s$ if $\sup_{x \in s} |\exp x| < \infty$, which is true since $\exp x > 0$ for all $x \in \mathbb{R}$

